### ✳ Style Guide – “Calm Focus” Journal Theme  

#### **Font system**
```css
font-family:
  --header-font: "Georgia", "Cambria", serif;
  --body-font: "Open Sans", "Calibri", "Avenir", sans-serif;
```

#### **Text hierarchy**
```css
h1, h2 { 
  font-family: var(--header-font);
  color: #355C7D;          /* gray‑blue accent */
  font-size: 1.4rem;       /* ≈ 14–16 pt */
  font-weight: 600;
  margin-top: 1.4em;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #C7CED9;
  padding-bottom: 0.2em;
}

body, p, li {
  font-family: var(--body-font);
  color: #222;             /* near‑black for readability */
  font-size: 1rem;         /* ≈ 11 pt */
  line-height: 1.6;
}

small, .disclaimer {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: #4B5B64;
}
```

#### **Color palette**
| Use | Color | Hex |
|:---|:---|:---|
| Accent headers / rules | Slate‑blue | `#355C7D` |
| Supporting accent | Forest‑green | `#3E6259` |
| Rule lines / borders | Pale‑gray | `#C7CED9` |
| Background | Warm off‑white | `#FAF9F7` |
| Link / highlight | Muted teal | `#5FA0A0` |

#### **Spacing guidelines**
```css
section {
  margin-bottom: 1.4em;
  padding-bottom: 0.6em;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #C7CED9;
}
```

#### **Extras**
- **Checkboxes:** 1 em square with border `#355C7D`; hover fill `#5FA0A0`.  
- **Input / text areas:** faint border `#C7CED9`; background `#FFFFFF`; padding 0.5 em.  
- **Page background:** `#FAF9F7` for calm contrast; maintain 1‑inch margins.

---

This palette and spacing keep the journal soft and readable, echoing the feel of printed therapeutic worksheets while still modern.  

